Package: ManyIVsNets
Type: Package
Title: Environmental Phillips Curve Analysis with Multiple Instrumental Variables and Networks
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2025-06-06
Authors@R: c(
    person("Avishek", "Bhandari", 
           email = "bavisek@gmail.com", 
           role = c("author", "maintainer"),
           comment = c(web = "avishekb9.github.io/econstellar"))
)
Description: Comprehensive toolkit for Environmental Phillips Curve (EPC) analysis 
    featuring multidimensional instrumental variable creation, transfer entropy 
    causal discovery, network analysis, and state-of-the-art econometric methods.
    Implements geographic, technological, migration, geopolitical, financial, 
    and natural risk instruments with robust diagnostics and visualization.
    Creates all instruments from scratch using economic and geographic data patterns,
    eliminating CSV file dependencies. Includes transfer entropy causal discovery,
    alternative state-of-the-art instruments (Spatial, Bartik, Migration, Shift-Share, 
    Gravity), and comprehensive network visualizations for publication-ready outputs.
